title: Friendly Zoo — Object-Detail Slot (ADR-195 S2)
story: friendly-zoo
description: The examine {slot:detail} channel — an examined object's traits stage state sentences (switchable hum, light-source beam) that the slot appends to its description at realize time. 0/1/N detail.

# ADR-195 S2: the examine action collects state-derived detail from the examined
# object's traits (the state-clauses registry) and stages it into the message's
# {slot:detail}. Off → no detail (clean); on → the trait sentences append.
---

# --- Reach the Supply Room (behind the locked staff gate) ---
> take keycard
[OK: contains "Taken"]
> south
[OK: contains "Main Path"]
> unlock gate with keycard
[OK: contains "unlock"]
> open gate
[OK: contains "open"]
> south
[OK: contains "Supply Room"]

# --- 0 detail: the radio is off; the slot is clean ---
> examine radio
[OK: contains "battered portable radio"]
[OK: not contains "It hums softly"]

# --- 1 detail: switched on, the radio's SwitchableTrait contributes one sentence ---
> turn on radio
[OK: contains "radio"]
> examine radio
[OK: contains "It hums softly."]

# --- 0 detail: the flashlight is off ---
> examine flashlight
[OK: contains "heavy-duty yellow flashlight"]
[OK: not contains "thin beam"]

# --- N detail: switched on lights it too, so two traits contribute two sentences ---
> turn on flashlight
[OK: contains "flashlight"]
> examine flashlight
[OK: contains "It clicks faintly as it powers up."]
[OK: contains "A thin beam plays across the floor."]
